/**
 * Vercel Ignore Configuration
 * 
 * Specifies files and directories to exclude from Vercel deployments.
 * This reduces deployment size and speeds up builds.
 * 
 * Similar to .gitignore but specifically for Vercel deployments.
 * Files listed here won't be uploaded to Vercel's build environment.
 * 
 * Categories:
 * 
 * 1. Dependencies (not needed - Vercel installs fresh)
 *    - node_modules/ - NPM packages
 *    - .pnp, .pnp.js - Yarn Plug'n'Play
 * 
 * 2. Testing (not needed in production)
 *    - coverage/ - Test coverage reports
 * 
 * 3. Next.js Build Output (rebuilt on Vercel)
 *    - .next/ - Development/production builds
 *    - out/ - Static export output
 * 
 * 4. Production Builds (rebuilt on Vercel)
 *    - build/, dist/ - Generic build directories
 * 
 * 5. System Files (not needed)
 *    - .DS_Store - macOS metadata
 *    - *.pem - Private keys (should be in env vars)
 * 
 * 6. Debug Logs (not needed)
 *    - npm-debug.log*, yarn-debug.log*, yarn-error.log*
 * 
 * 7. Local Environment Files (use Vercel env vars instead)
 *    - .env.local - Local development variables
 *    - .env.development.local - Development overrides
 *    - .env.test.local - Test environment
 *    - .env.production.local - Production overrides
 * 
 * 8. Vercel Configuration (already in Vercel)
 *    - .vercel - Vercel deployment metadata
 * 
 * 9. TypeScript Build Cache (rebuilt on Vercel)
 *    - *.tsbuildinfo - Incremental build info
 * 
 * 10. Documentation (not needed in production)
 *     - *.md - Markdown files (except README.md)
 *     - !README.md - Keep README for reference
 * 
 * 11. Test Files (not needed in production)
 *     - test-aws-connection.js - AWS connection test
 *     - debug.log - Debug output
 * 
 * Benefits:
 * - Faster deployments (smaller upload size)
 * - Reduced build time
 * - Lower bandwidth usage
 * - Cleaner deployment environment
 * 
 * @see https://vercel.com/docs/concepts/projects/project-configuration#vercelignore
 */

# Dependencies
node_modules
.pnp
.pnp.js

# Testing
coverage

# Next.js
.next/
out/

# Production
build
dist

# Misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# Debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Local env files
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Vercel
.vercel

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# Documentation (not needed in production)
*.md
!README.md

# Test files
test-aws-connection.js
debug.logconnection.js
debug.log
